text:
The cause of the accident was determined to be the pilot's intentional flight into known adverse weather conditions.
On January 12, 1994, an Agusta-Bell 206A-1 crashed while attempting to land at the helipad of the Central Command headquarters in Neve Yaakov, killing all four occupants on board, including IDF Major General Nehemiah Tamari.
On July 10, 2002, a Bell 206 LIII of the Cyprus national guard, carrying two pilots and five passengers, including the chief of the National Guard, Lt. Gen. Evangelos Florakis, crashed after on air fire, near Kouklia village, Pafos, close to Andreas Papandreou air base, killing all on board.
On March 9, 2009, Bangladesh Army aviation unit Bell 206L flown by pilot Lt Col MD Shahidul Islam and co-pilot Major Saif crashed at Rouha in Kalihati sub-district.
